text: Wynnewood is a suburban unincorporated community, located west of Philadelphia, in Montgomery County, Pennsylvania and Delaware County, Pennsylvania, United States. The community was named in 1691 for Dr. Thomas Wynne, William Penn's physician and the first Speaker of the Pennsylvania General Assembly. As of 2020 census, there were 15,390 people living here. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Pennsylvania
title: Wynnewood, Pennsylvania
